  "prompt": "What are the chances of the electoral college changing vote for Clinton?",
  "response": "As of December 2016, the chances of the Electoral College dramatically changing the outcome of the presidential election and selecting Hillary Clinton instead of Donald Trump were extremely low. While some Clinton supporters and electors discussed the possibility of \"faithless electors\" who might vote differently than their state's popular vote, there was not a realistic path to changing the election result. Trump won 304 electoral votes to Clinton's 227, and would have needed a significant number of electors to switch their votes to prevent his victory. In the end, only a small number of individual electors voted differently than expected, but not enough to alter the overall outcome of the election.",
